Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of electronic media and the World-Wide Web for documenting and describing language, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the infrastructure for distributed archiving of language resources, which involves issues related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The governance infrastructure for expressing consensus on recommended best practices may also involve machine learning (cs.LG) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) considerations.
